Project: dicthelp
Intention: Refer the dictionary and suggest correct word(s) for 
           a given misspelled word
Start Date: 16th Dec 2011
Language: C


Usage: dicthelp [OPTION]... word

Options:
        -d <dictionary>
           Specify name of the dictionary to look up the
           word/suggestions into
           *Default dictionary = /usr/share/dict/words
        -s [r|a]
           Set sort-order of the output
           r  sorts suggested words accordig to the relevancy (edit-distance)
           a  sorts suggested words alphabetically
           *Default sort order = r
        -f Force suggestions.
           Show suggestions (similarly spelled words) even if the supplied word is
           spelled correctly.
           *By default -f is not in effect.
        -h Show this help
Advanced Options:
        -t n
           Set max edit-distance threshold
           n is edit-distance (a numeric value)
           Only suggestions with edit-distance less than or equal to n will be shown
           Higher the value of n, more suggestions (with reduced relevancy)
           *Default threshold value is 2
 EXAMPLES:
 dicthelp happyness
 dicthelp -t 3 happyness
 dicthelp -t 3 -sa happyness
